A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Dr. Robert Gordon Ross McInally; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Dr. Robert Gordon Ross McInally joined the Rotary Club of South
3 Queensferry, Scotland, in 1984 and has since held prominent leadership roles such as
4 President and Vice President of Rotary International in Great Britain and Ireland; and
5 WHEREAS, during his distinguished tenure, Dr. McInally spearheaded a partnership with
6 Hope and Homes for Children, focusing on providing stability and support for Rwandan
7 genocide orphans, and he continues to serve as a patron of the organization; and
8 WHEREAS, Dr. McInally further serves as a patron of Trade-Aid, an initiative of the Rotary
9 Club of Grantham Kesteven, England, which delivers sustainable humanitarian aid to the
10 developing world, as well as an ambassador for Bipolar UK; and
11 WHEREAS, this distinguished gentleman has given inspiration to many through his high
12 ideals, morals, and deep concern for his fellow citizens, and he possesses the vast wisdom
13 which only comes through experience and the strength of character which is achieved
14 through overcoming the many challenges of life; and
